Israeli prime minister says Donald Trump responded to 'another important request of mine, which serves the interests of our countries and countries of the region.' JERUSALEM - Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu  on Monday lauded the US decision to designate Iran's Revolutionary Guards a terrorist organisation, saying President Donald Trump had responded to a "request of mine." "Thank you, my dear friend, US President Donald Trump, for having decided to declare Iran's Revolutionary Guards a terrorist organisation," Netanyahu said in a statement a day ahead of Israeli elections in which he is seeking a fifth term. "Thank you for responding to another important request of mine, which serves the interests of our countries and countries of the region."